HEADWORD: minicomputer
<hw>minicomputer</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Computers)</fld> <def>a
mid-sized digital computer; at any given point in the development of
computer technology, a <ex>minicomputer</ex> will be faster and have
greater capacity than a <contr>microcomputer</contr>, but will be slower
and have less capacity than a <contr>mainframe
computer</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
